<UserControl xmlns="https://github.com/avaloniaui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
             xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
             xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
             mc:Ignorable="d" d:DesignWidth="800" d:DesignHeight="450"
             x:Class="StellarMVVM_2024.Views.inflation_archive_screen">
	<UserControl.Styles>
		<StyleInclude Source="/Styles/archive info styles/inflation_archive_stylesheet.axaml"/>
	</UserControl.Styles>
	<Panel Background="Pink">
		<StackPanel
		HorizontalAlignment="Center"
		Name="inflationArchiveStackPanel">
			<TextBlock
				Classes="title"
				PointerReleased="returnPrevious">
				inflation
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				1. inflation occurs when there is too much money in the economic circulation
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				2. essentially, your money is worth less
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				3. when all people have more money, prices go up so suppliers can make more relative profit
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				4. to battle inflation, the government increases taxes people have to pay
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				5. increase of taxes result in less spending money people have. that means: less money in the circulation
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				6. to calculate inflation rate, look at a product price from two different years (same product)
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				7. take the difference, divide it by the original price. multiply the quotient by one hundred for the rate
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				8. when all people have more money, prices go up so suppliers can make more relative profit
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				9. a negative inflation rate signals deflation (your money is worth more)
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				10.inflation usually occurs when there is high demand for something
			</TextBlock>
		</StackPanel>
	</Panel>
</UserControl>
